Package soot.jimple.infoflow.android.source.parsers.xml

Class XMLSourceSinkParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.source.parsers.xml.AbstractXMLSourceSinkParser
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.source.parsers.xml.XMLSourceSinkParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISourceSinkDefinitionProvider
    public class XMLSourceSinkParser
extends AbstractXMLSourceSinkParser
implements ISourceSinkDefinitionProvider
    Parses informations from the new Dataformat (XML) with the help of SAX. Returns only a Set of Android Method when calling the function parse. For the AccessPath the class SaxHandler is used.
    Author:
    Anna-Katharina Wickert, Joern Tillmans, Steven Arzt, Niklas Vogel

        Factory method for MethodSourceSinkDefinition instances
        Specified by:
        createMethodSourceSinkDefinition in class AbstractXMLSourceSinkParser
        Parameters:
        method - The method that is to be defined as a source or sink
        baseAPs - The access paths rooted in the base object that shall be considered as sources or sinks
        paramAPs - The access paths rooted in parameters that shall be considered as sources or sinks. The index in the set corresponds to the index of the formal parameter to which the respective set of access paths belongs.
        returnAPs - The access paths rooted in the return object that shall be considered as sources or sinks
        callType - The type of call (normal call, callback, etc.)
        Returns:
        The newly created MethodSourceSinkDefinition instance
